path.desc: A wave of smell washes over you as you open the door. It’s horrible enough to make you physically shudder. It is the stench of death and rot.

path.desc: Window shutters are closed. The storm is raging outside.

path.desc: Cloth bound handful of wedding cookies hidden under the pillow.
Nights stand. Candle. Small praying book in the drawer.
Night stand. Whetstone and a small knife made shiny and thin by constant sharpening.
Sheets are stained and smelly. Not repulsive, but not exactly clean.
High leather boots. Black leather apron. Fishing pole and a box of baits.
One small rugged dress. Five empty hangers.
Chest. Twenty eight ducats inside along with a ????
Beautiful wedding dress of soft creamy color. Lacing seems torn. Few blood droplets sully the skirt.
Wooden washbowl, scrubbing board and blood stained sheets. Water smells stale and rotten.

path.onmouseout: You breath a small cloud of mist into the cold room. Maybe there is something else around here.
path.onmouseover: Pretentious style and the smell are a bit uncomfortable, but the dress will at least help you keep some of the heat.
path.desc: Large woven laundry basket. Would you like to dress in an unwashed clothes?
Worktable with a bowl of crystallized sandarac, bottled linseed oil, burner, two rough brushes and a narrow file.
Tool closet. Inside a selection of woodworking and a few gardening tools, including an axe.
Once expensive oriental carpet worn down by time and dust.
Family banner. Deep green background with a silver manticore.
Family banner. Deep green background with a silver manticore.
Padded wooden bench.
Padded wooden bench with nail marks along the armrests.

path.onmouseover: Even the camembert and smoked sausages couldn’t overpower the stench from cook’s body. But at least you are no longer hungry.
path.onmouseout: Your stomach is voting otherwise, but okay.
path.desc: Food rack. Salted meat, salami, vegetables, fruits, honey and more. Some is starting to rot, but there is still a lot of good food. Eat?
Sacks of flour.
Barrel half filled with candles. Various colors and sizes.
Flour-sprinkled kitchen table. Cutting board, a knife, plate with fruits, three mold-ridden strudels.
Small table. Plate, rotten meat, wide bottle of what seems to be barbecue sauce.
Shelf. Packs, pouches and vials for various spices.
Built in grill.
Empty washbowl. Thin layer of white-blue mold on the bottom.
Barrel. Empty. Smells of oil.
Bucket.
Cupboard. Selection of both fine cutlery and porcelain dishes.
Pair of wall hangers. Apron on one of them.

path.onmouseover: Bloated corpse releases all kinds of liquids and gasses as you turn it over. There are no signs of struggle, just two stab wounds in the back just below the ribs.
path.onmouseout: His surprised wide eyes will surely visit you again in dreams. No need to disturb the dead any more.
path.desc: Corpse of a man. Cooking apron, round features and short black hair stuck to a puddle of dried blood. Examine the body?

path.onmouseover: Radiating heat slowly relaxes your muscles.
path.onmouseout: You are wet and cold. But maybe staying unnoticed is worth it. Who knows who could see the smoke.
path.desc: Arched fireplace. Wood burned all the way to the ashes. Do you want to start a fresh fire?
Glorious plate armor. Looks only decorative on the closer inspection. The thin metal is polished iron and tin and the gilding is just bronze instead of gold.

Uncomfortably long dining table for a dinner in two. One side looks much better attended, various meals flow from plate to plate all bitten once or twice and left to rot. Horsewhip casually leans on the side.
Padded chair.
Padded chair.
Padded chair.
Padded chair.
Padded chair.
Padded chair.
Firewood rack.
Carpet. Thick and warm.
Tall decorative vase. Empty.
Tall decorative vase. Empty.
Lord Waylan Korsh enjoying his grand hunt. Horses and dogs racing through the forest after an unknown prey.
Portrait of a beautiful young lady. Blond hair barely covering sad and swolen eyes.
Portrait of a tall well dressed woman. She looks ambitious and competent but stares into nothing like a broken child or a veteran soldier.
Portrait of a girl. Chubby and cute, big eyes, curly hair. Her smile is a little too forced and the corset looks painfully tight.
Sandarac polished oak stairs. Want to go upstairs?
Bar cabinet. Box of tobacco, few bottles of brandy.
bear skin rug
Stuffed bear.
Short round table with a pipe and invitation to an antique auction.
Cushioned chair.
Head of a large catfish.
Boar head.
Fox head.

Deer head flinches and bares it’s teeth as you come close. It has empty glass eyes, but the rest seems perfectly animated and alive. Nostrils flare, ears twitch and jaw moves naturally as it speaks “Greetings master, you wish to join the dead?”
Large boar head and torso.
Fish head.
Window shutters are closed. The storm is raging outside.
Fire poker.

Marble statue of a serious man. Proud face, strong posture, long coat. The ancient hunting spear is of black iron and inseparable from the statue. The text says “Lord Waylan Korsh, master of the five hills.”

path.onmouseout: Wise, maybe it's just a trap.
path.desc: Hidden in plain sight. One of the stones is a button for a secret entrance. Push it and enter?

path.onmouseout: Is't it just your fear talking?

path.desc: Cellar entrance. Do you want to go down there?
